===Etymology===
From [[bawl]] + [[out]]

===Transitive verb=== 
'''bawl out''' 

# To deliver a loud hard scolding or [[lecture]].
#:''After a mistake like that, there wasn't much to do besides '''bawl out''' the offender and clean up.''
# To have a serious [[argument]] accompanied with shouting.


===Alternative forms===
Noun: '''bawling out''', ''plural:'' '''bawling outs'''): a loud scolding or argument

